 data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104khp1665702939925.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/khp1665702939925.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/khp1665702939925.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"khp1665702939925\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n       Key Management on Informix\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Primary keys are created using the primary key constraints defined during table\n      creation. Primary key constraint names follow the same naming convention as index\n      names.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"khp1665702939925__p_d50741e1_d50742e1_d50743e1\">Candidate key are created using the unique constraints defined during table creation. The constraint names follow the same naming convention as index names.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"khp1665702939925__p_d50744e1_d50745e1_d50746e1\">The table lists the rules for both primary and candidate keys:</p>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Rules for primary keys</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Rules for keys</p>\n</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Required by DBMS</p>\n</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Must be contiguous</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Primary and candidate keys allowed to overlap</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">Yes</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__1\">\n<p class=\"p\">Primary keys mandatory</p>\n</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"khp1665702939925__table_d4700e1_d4701e1_d4702e1__entry__2\">\n<p class=\"p\">No</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"khp1665702939925__section_wbf_yr2_jcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d802031e136\">Storage Formats Allowed for Key Fields</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"khp1665702939925__p_d50750e1_d50751e1_d50752e1\">All storage formats are allowed for primary or\n            candidate key fields except Text and Byte. Some combinations of Uniface data types and\n            packing codes are not suitable (Boolean fields, for example).</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529211\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2529211\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Key Management on Informix Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Key Management on Informix Primary keys are created using the primary key constraints defined during table creation. Primary key constraint names follow the same naming convention as index names. Candidate key are created using the unique constraints defined during table creation. The constraint names follow the same naming convention as index names. The table lists the rules for both primary and candidate keys: Table 1. Rules for primary keys Rules for keys Required by DBMS Must be contiguous No Primary and candidate keys allowed to overlap Yes Primary keys mandatory No Storage Formats Allowed for Key Fields All storage formats are allowed for primary or candidate key fields except Text and Byte. Some combinations of Uniface data types and packing codes are not suitable (Boolean fields, for example). Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}